results.title: Baca; The Treaty of Hidalgo
results.snippet:
This story map details the events leading up to the signing of The Treaty of Guadalupe Hidalgo in 1848, it contains copies of the written treaty, and identifies key figures and dates associated with this event.
The Treaty of Guadalupe Hidalgo was signed at the Villa de Guadalupe Hidalgo, and is a peace treaty signed on the 2nd day of February, 1848. The treaty ended the war between the United States and Mexico. By the treatys' terms, Mexico ceded over 525,00 square miles of land along their northern border. The U.S. acquisition amounted to 55% of Mexico's land and ultimately was the biggest acquisition in american history. The cession included several states presently known as Colorado, Arizona, New Mexico, Utah, Nevada, Texas, and Wyoming. In addition, as part of the treaty terms, the United States paid Mexico 15 million dollars compensation and forgave another 3.25 million of mexico's debt.
